'''Dulwich Hill Interchange MLR station''' is a planned light rail stop located in the southern part of the suburb of [[Dulwich Hill, New South Wales|Dulwich Hill]] on the [[Metro Light Rail]] line in [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]]. The stop is planned for completion in 2012. The extension will operate from the current light rail terminus at [[Lilyfield MLR station|Lilyfield]] making use of the former Rozelle branch of the [[Metropolitan Goods railway line]] heavy rail freight corridor.<ref>[http://www.transport.nsw.gov.au/rail/lightrail-extension.html Sydney Light Rail Extensions - Transport NSW]</ref><ref>[http://www.transport.nsw.gov.au/sites/default/file/rail/SLRE-Community-Update-July-August-2010.pdf Community Update - Light Rail Extension - Inner West, Lilyfield to Dulwich Hill, July/August 2010]</ref> Dulwich Hill Interchange is located at the end of the closed section of the goods line and is thus the terminus of the light rail extension. The name is intended to highlight the connection with [[Dulwich Hill railway station]] which will be a short walk from the light rail stop.
